overall_summary: The reasoning trajectory demonstrates a practical approach to time-series forecasting focused on handling strong daily seasonality with limited data. It prioritizes simplicity and interpretability by selecting a baseline method after considering more complex models, with thorough attention to data patterns, computational steps, and output formatting.
common_data_patterns: No missing values in input data
key_insights: Identification of daily seasonality as the dominant pattern for model selection
Preference for simple methods (Seasonal Naive with averaging) over complex models due to limited data size
Hourly averaging technique to smooth variations while preserving daily cycles
Detailed rounding protocols to maintain data precision consistency
Explicit handling of datetime generation for multi-period forecasts
complexity_analysis: Moderately complex with detailed computational steps; balances advanced model awareness with practical implementation of baseline methods. Includes data grouping, statistical calculations, and rounding logic while avoiding unnecessary sophistication.
